TextArea((24.0, 548.0), (72.0, 118.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"Good evening from the Arnolfini in Bristol and welcome to the Sky News leaders' debate, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'round two of the first ever televised prime ministerial debates in the UK. The three men who ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'want to run the country after May 6th are here and raring to go, so please welcome David ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Cameron, Nick Clegg and Gordon Brown. APPLAUSE ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 557.0), (130.0, 187.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'The agreed theme for the first half of this debate is international affairs. Each leader will make ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'a short opening statement before taking questions from the audience. In the second half ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"tonight, we'll move on to general issues. Lots have been drawn to decide who goes first. We " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'begin with the current Prime Minister and leader of the Labour Party, Gordon Brown. Mr ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Brown.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (199.0, 313.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"This may have the feel of a TV popularity contest, but in truth, this is an election about Britain's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"future, a fight for your future, and for your jobs. If it's all about style and PR, count me out. If it's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"about the big decisions, if it's about judgment, it's delivering a better future for this country, I'm " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'your man. Ahead are huge challenges, delivering the economic recovery in jobs, bringing our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'brave troops safely home from Afghanistan, keeping our streets free of terrorism, building ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'alliances in Europe against nuclear weapons, against climate change, against poverty and to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'deal with our banks. Now, not everyone has the answers, but I say get the big decisions wrong ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and Britain's security and jobs are at risk. Get the big decisions right, and we can have a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'prosperous, fairer, greener and better Britain. Like me or not, I can deliver that plan. The way ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to do it is with a majority Labour government.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 510.0), (326.0, 337.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you, Mr Brown. Next, the leader of the Conservative Party, David Cameron.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (349.0, 487.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"Thank you. It's clear from last week's debate that the country wants change. But the question " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"is, what sort of change and who's best placed to lead that change? If you vote Conservative, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you will get a new team running the country from May 7th. And you won't be stuck with what " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you've got now. But real change comes from your values, and there, there are big differences " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'between us. I believe that we need to do more to help families. They are the absolute bedrock ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'of a strong society. I want government to be accountable. I want less waste, less bureaucracy. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Stopping the jobs tax, but making sure we have good public services that you get good value ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"for money for. As we're going to discuss tonight, I want us to keep our defences strong, I want " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to keep our borders secure and our country safe. But real change, real change comes not just ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"from politicians, but from when we all recognise that we have responsibilities. We're all in this " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"together, and that's how we will build the big and strong society I believe we need in our " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'country. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 525.0), (489.0, 512.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you, Mr Cameron. And finally in this round, Nick Clegg, the leader of the Liberal ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Democrats. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (524.0, 638.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'I am so proud of the values that have made our country so great. Democracy, human rights, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the rule of law. But the sad truth is that in recent years, our governments under the old parties ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"have let those values down. We shouldn't have sent soldiers into battle without the right " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"equipment. We shouldn't be facing allegations of complicity in torture, we shouldn't have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'invaded Iraq. So I want us to lead in the world. I want us to lead in Europe, not complain from ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the sidelines. I want us to lead in creating a world free of nuclear weapons. And I want us to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'lead on the biggest challenge of all, climate change. My family knows what British values really ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'mean. My mother was freed by British troops from a prisoner of war camp. And I think, if we do ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'things differently, we can be proud, once again, of the role we can play as a force for good in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the world. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 555.0), (639.0, 719.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"Thank you, Mr Clegg. Those are tonight's opening statements. Now it's time for the questions " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'from the audience. The audience here is made up mainly of local voters from the south-west, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'some with allegiances, others yet to be persuaded. There will also be some questions in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'person from Sky News viewers who e-mailed us. Each leader has a uninterrupted minute to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'answer each question, followed by a second minute to deal with what their rivals have said. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Then it's free debate time with no guaranteed time at the microphone. Now, our first question " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"comes from Christopher Nelms, who's from Saltford, near Bristol. Mr Nelms.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 554.0), (728.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u"Hello, I'm Chris Nelms, I work in the building trade. I can't see any advantage of us being in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Europe. I think there's far too much interference politically and legally, and I just wonder what " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'you intend to do to stop it?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 385.0), (72.0, 83.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'How are you going to tackle Europe, David Cameron?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (95.0, 244.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"Very directly, Christopher, I think we should be in Europe, because we're a trading nation, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we're part of Europe, we want to co-operate and work with our allies in Europe to get things " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'done. But I do agree with you that we have let too many powers go from Westminster to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Brussels, we've  passed too much power over and we should take some of those powers back. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"I want us to be in Europe but not run by Europe. There will... you'll hear big differences " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"between me and the other two parties. I don't want us to join the euro, I want I want us to keep " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the pound as our currency. I don't want us to give up the British rebate. I want to make sure we " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'get value for money for what we put into Europe. I want to cut some of the bureaucracy, some ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"of the rules, some of the regulations that I think drive business so mad. That's the agenda " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you'd get from a Conservative government in Europe. To those who say somehow this would " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'be isolation, I say nonsense. President Sarkozy of France, he stands up for France in Europe. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Angela Merkel in Germany, she stands up for Germany in Europe. I would do exactly the same ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'for Europe.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 252.0), (256.0, 267.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. Nick Clegg?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (279.0, 417.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'I actually worked for the man who was sent by Margaret Thatcher, would you believe it, to bat ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'for Britain in Brussels. What I learned when I was there was this: the European Union is not ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'perfect - of course not. This is a club that took 15 years to define "chocolate" in a chocolate ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'directive. Anything that takes 15 years to define chocolate is not a model of democratic ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'efficiency. What I also learned was this, that there are a whole load of things, whether we like it ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"or not, whatever your views on Europe and the european Union, which we simply can't do on " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"our own. We can't deal with international crime that touches and affects every single " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"community in this country on our own. We can't deal with climate change on our own. The " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"weather doesn't stop at the cliffs of Dover. We can't regulate these wretched banks that got us " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"into so much in the first place which now sprawl across countries. I don't think the European " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Union is perfect. I want it reformed, that's why I want to lead in the European Union. But we're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"stronger together and we're weaker apart.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 195.0), (420.0, 431.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Mr Brown?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (443.0, 580.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"You know, there's three million reasons why we need to be part of the European Union, and " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"they're called jobs. Three million jobs depend on our membership of the European Union. Half " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"our trade is with the European Union. 750,000 businesses - I'm sorry it's not your business, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'raising the question about the building trade - but 750,000 businesses trade with Europe. The ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'idea that we should again be isolated and on the margins and not in the mainstream of Europe ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'would be a terrible, terrible mistake. Now, I worked with the European leaders through the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'global financial crisis. I had to persuade them that we had to restructure our banks and they ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'had to restructure their banks. I had to persuade them they had to work with America in the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'G20, but when Europe and America works together, we are so much stronger. Stronger to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'deal with climate change, which is one much my priorities, stronger to deal with the economy, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'stronger to deal with international crime, stronger to deal with terrorism, let us never again be ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"an empty chair in Europe. My fear is that David's policy would put us in that position.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 274.0), (592.0, 603.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. David Cameron?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 556.0), (615.0, 764.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'I understand why people like Christopher are frustrated about the European Union and some ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'of the things that have happened. I think one of the reasons that people are so angry is that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'politicians at Westminster have given away powers to Brussels without asking us, the people, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'first. I think people felt particularly cheated when the European constitution came forward and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we were told we were going to get a referendum and Gordon Brown and Labour stopped that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"from happening and Nick Clegg and the Liberal Democrats didn't vote with us to get that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'referendum. We should have had one. People feel cheated by that. As a result, one of the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'things I would do if I was your Prime Minister is straightaway pass a law through parliament ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"that says if ever there's a future occasion when laws are being proposed to pass power from " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Westminster to Brussels, there will be a guarantee of a referendum held in our country. You ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"send us to parliament to make decisions, make laws, discuss the issues, yes. You don't send " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'us there to give away powers that belong to you. There should be a referendum guarantee if ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'ever this happens again.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 242.0), (212.0, 223.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. Mr Clegg.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (235.0, 373.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'David Cameron talks about a guarantee. It was the Conservative Party that gave a cast iron ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'guarantee to have a referendum on the Lisbon Treaty which it promptly dropped. Look, we do ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"need to have a referendum the next time there's a big transfer of powers to the European " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Union but it needs to be on the fundamental issue: do we stay in or do we go out? You have a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"right to make that choice in a referendum. I would argue we should stay in, not because it's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"perfect but because it's in our interests to do so. Let me give you, Christopher, a very concrete " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'example. There was some time agoa operation by European police authorities which broke ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'open a paedophile ring. They arrested 100 sex offenders, many of them in this country. And ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'they released 20 young women from unimaginable abuse and servitude. something called ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Operation Koala. ou can Google it and look it up. Guess what? Conservative MEPs, UK ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Independence Party MEPs voted against the measures which made that possible. That is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"putting dogma above the safety of children. We are safer together, we're weaker apart.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 214.0), (385.0, 396.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (408.0, 546.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Imagine a European Council meeting if David Cameron was in in charge two months from ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"now. He'd have to go along as he said and say he wanted to repatriate the social chapter. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"That's what gives us paid holidays. He'd have to break up the European Union meeting and " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'say, "Look, 26 of you are against this, I\'m the only one who\'s standign for this". And what ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'would happen? We are trying to get an economic recovery. That depends on economic ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'recovery, depending on Germany, France and other countries growing as well.  Taking our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'exports. We have to get an agreement on climate change because of what happened at ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Copenhagen. Again, that would be postponed because we would be having a big argument as ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we did in the past with a Conservative government about repatriating powers in Britain. We've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"got other props we've got to deal with and these include security and terrorism. These are the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"issues. Let's look to the future. Let's not have a Britain-only solution and let's not go back to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the days when we were fighting with the rest of Europe in the past. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 341.0), (548.0, 559.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"David, it's over to you now for a free debate.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (571.0, 651.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"What I would say is what you're hearing from the other two is frankly don't trust the people, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"don't ask them when you pass powers from Westminster to Brussels, just give in to everything " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"that comes out of Brussels and don't stand up for your country. That to me is the same old " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'politics. Let me just ask this important point: this idea that somehow an in-out referendum is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"what the public wants I don't think is right, it's a con. What people want when a new treaty " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'comes along, when a constitution comes along, is to have that choice to vote on that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'constitution. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (72.0, 198.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"No, no. Let's be clear. What would have been a con would be to have a referendum on one " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"individual treaty, which, even if we'd had the referendum, and then we'd rejected the treaty, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"would have allowed, Christopher, the European Union to carry on exactly as before. Let's have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the fundamental debate. I worked in my previous life before going into politics for a while as a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'negotiator on behalf of all of us, on behalf of Britain and the European Union, negotiating trade ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'deals with the Chinese government, the Russian government and others. What I noticed there ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'was that the Chinese and the Russians, they only listened to what we were saying because I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'was representing the largest single market in the world of 475 million consumers. Now, of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'course there are daft rules, of course it does daft things, but it seems to me that we punch ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"above our weight when we stand together in Europe in a world, frankly, where you've got a lot " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'of superpowers bumping up against each other and where, to coin a phrase, size does matter.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (212.0, 316.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"You see, David wants a referendum if there's any future change; Nick wants a referendum now " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'on the European Union. I think what people want is us to solve the employment problem, the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'economic problem and get on with the job. I need to work with these other countries in Europe ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"- President Sarkozy, Chancellor Merkel. David's walked away from the European People's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Party, which is an alliance of the centre, progressive parties in Europe, and gone in with a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'group of right-wing extremists. I want to work with the sensible people in Europe to get jobs for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"our British economy. If we don't trade with Europe, we lose jobs, we lose businesses, we lose " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"growth. Let's make sure our priority trading with Europe, sorting out the problems of the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"European Union, yes, but let's make sure we get a recovery that's stronger than ever. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 205.0), (327.0, 338.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Mr Cameron.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (350.0, 442.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"You can hear there is a difference, there's a real difference between us. The reason about this " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"European party is I just think it's the hypocrisy that people are fed up with, of British politicians " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'standing here in Bristol saying, "I\'m going to stand up for us in Europe and we shouldn\'t give ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'away all these powers and we should fight for British interest," and then over they go to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Brussels and they do exactly the opposite. I want to make sure we say the same thing when ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we're in Bristol, about wanting to be in Europe but not run by Europe, wanting to have a single " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"market that's good for our country, wanting to trade with Europe, but not go over to Brussels " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and say something different. It's that, the same old politics... " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (452.0, 509.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'How on earth does it help anyone in Bristol or anyone else in the country for that matter, David ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Cameron, to join together in the European Union with a bunch of nutters, anti-Semites, people ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"who deny climate change exists, homophobes. That doesn't help Britain. Of course we need to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"change the European Union, but you change clubs of which you're a member by getting stuck " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'in, not standing on the side-lines and complaining about things.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 362.0), (521.0, 532.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'What the Liberal Democrats have actually done... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 340.0), (534.0, 545.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'I think Gordon Brown wants to come in first.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (557.0, 580.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'You know who these two guys remind me? They remind me of my two young boys squabbling ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'at bath time. And the squabbling about... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 283.0), (591.0, 602.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"That's a good line in rehearsal.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 289.0), (614.0, 625.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"I think we're past bath time now!  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 551.0), (637.0, 695.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Squabbling about whether to have referendums on the European Union. What we need is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'jobs, and growth, and economic recovery. We work with our partners to get that. The sooner ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Nick realised also we had to work with America and Europe to get economic growth in the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"future, the better. I'm afraid David is anti-European, Nick is anti-American, and both of them " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'are out of touch with reality.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 551.0), (72.0, 129.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"It's not a question of... It's a question of wanting to get things in Europe for your country and " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'standing up for your country. One of the things the Liberal Democrats would want to do is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"actually take away Britain's seat on the United Nations Security Council and replace it with a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"European one. That's one of the things that actually gives us the ability to punch above our " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'weight in the world. It gives us influence in the world... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 351.0), (141.0, 152.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"David, David, you're running up the wrong line. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 437.0), (154.0, 165.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'A final quick word from first of all Gordon Brown, then Nick Clegg.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (177.0, 222.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'There is no chance of Britain giving up its seat on the United Nations Security Council. We are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"stronger, we've just been chairman of the G20 as a result of the efforts we made in the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"economy. We're leading the negotiations on climate change and we're leading on nuclear non-" FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'proliferation. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 314.0), (235.0, 246.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Nick Clegg, final word. Anti-American? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 558.0), (258.0, 303.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I'd simply say don't let people create scare stories to frighten you into thinking that we can't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'change Europe. Of course we can change Europe. I, unlike David Cameron and Gordon ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Brown, have been in there, have sought changes. We can do it if we leave and don't complain " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'on the side-lines. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (308.0, 331.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"We're going to have to move on now. Now, question B comes from Stuart Wolvin from Horfield " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'in Bristol. Stuart. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (343.0, 366.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u'Thank you. Given our involvement in Afghanistan, if there is another multinational operation to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'remove Al-Qaeda or another terrorist group from a failed state, would the UK participate?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 536.0), (378.0, 400.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'So, will the UK take part in future multinational operations against terrorists abroad? Nick ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Clegg.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (412.0, 550.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Clearly, the principle of the reason why we went into Afghanistan, why I supported our mission ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'in Afghanistan, unlike the illegal invasion in Iraq, is to keep us safe. Not to parachute ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"democracy into Afghanistan, it's because we believe that if you allow Afghanistan to be a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'haven of extremism and terrorism, there will be more terrorist attacks here in Britain. So, from ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that principle, if we need to do that again, we should. The problem, of course, is we have done ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"it in a manner where I don't think we've pursued the right strategy, we haven't given the right " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"equipment to our troops. We haven't had proper international co-ordination on the ground in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Afghanistan, we haven't worked properly with other countries in the region to do so. I think if " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you put soldiers into harm's way, you either do the job properly or you don't do it at all. If we " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"ever take that decision again, let's make sure we've got the right equipment, the right strategy, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"so they can come back having done the job we've asked them to do, with their heads held " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'high, knowing they have done the job well.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 266.0), (552.0, 563.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. Gordon Brown.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (575.0, 724.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"I want to answer the question directly. Let's be honest, and Nick didn't say this, we've already " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"got Al-Qaeda in Somalia, we've already got problems with Al-Qaeda in Yemen. We are having " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to take action with our multilateral partners to deal with these problems, and will continue to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'have to do so. Why are we in Afghanistan, and why we have we got to be vigilant all the time? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'The reason is, there is a chain of terror that links these Al-Qaeda groups in different parts of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the world to action that could happen in the United Kingdom. Every week I get a report, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'sometimes every day, of terrorist plots, most of which arise in the Afghanistan/Pakistan area, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and we have got to deal with. To keep the streets safe in Britain, we have to take on Al-Qaeda ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'wherever it is. I also have to say about Afghanistan that this is a mission that can work. The ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'reason is, we are training up the Afghan soldiers and the Afghan police. So whenever we are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'in a mission abroad, we have to make sure that we have a means by which, in that country, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'they can build up their own security staff, so we can bring our troops home. That is my ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'mission, that is my aim.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 268.0), (736.0, 747.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. David Cameron. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (72.0, 210.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Stuart asked, would we participate. If I was your Prime Minister, I would want to think very ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"carefully what's in the national interest, what will make us safer here in the United Kingdom? I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'think we need to end the division between foreign policy and security policy and Home Office ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'policy. Bring it all together and think about our national security. I would also say this. If you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'look at future operations like that, we have to learn from the mistakes of the past. We have to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"make sure we plan properly, we've got to make sure we never send our troops into battle " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'again without the proper equipment, without the proper helicopters. We have to think through ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'not just what we are doing militarily, but actually is the aid there, are we helping these people? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Do we have a political strategy for how we are going to get out of that country once we have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'tried to make it safe with our allies? In the case of Afghanistan, far too many of those ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"questions weren't answered. And even now, while I support what we are doing and I want it to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'work, I still worry we are not doing enough to get the political situation right in Afghanistan.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 187.0), (222.0, 233.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Mr Clegg. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (245.0, 382.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I think everyone is agreed that if we were to do this again, which is Stuart's question, we need " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to make sure that we've got the right equipment, the right resources. That's why I think it is " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'essential that after the next election, whoever wins, there is a full defence review, so we have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'a real good look at where we are spending money, whether we are spending it wisely and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'whether we are providing the troops on the frontline with the resources they need. I personally ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"think that we're not spending money on some of the right things. I wouldn't carry on spending " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'money on the Eurofighter Typhoon, the third tranche of that Eurofighter project, consuming ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"billions of pounds. I don't think it's right to do what both David Cameron and Gordon Brown " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'want, which is now to commit, before we need to make a decision, to spend up to \xa3100 billion ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'renewing, exactly in the same old way, the Cold War Trident nuclear missile system. If you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"take decisions like that, then maybe you can equip our troops so they don't get so terribly " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'overstretched, as they were in fighting two wars on two fronts in Iraq and in Afghanistan.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 211.0), (394.0, 405.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (417.0, 543.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'My first thoughts will always be for our troops, for our dedicated forces, our professional ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'forces. Every day I meet people who have got people serving in Afghanistan or have served in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'other parts of the world. We have got to do everything we can to support them, yes there will ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'be a defence review in the next parliament, so we can do our best by our forces. Look, what ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'happened on Christmas Eve was a bomber who would have been in Detroit and bombing that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'plane, came from Somalia. That was really where he was given his orders from. So we have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"got to deal with Al-Qaeda in Somalia and Yemen, as well as in Pakistan. We've got to be clear, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that we cannot allow terrorists to have territory in the world that then they use as a base for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'attacking the United Kingdom. I will do everything in my power to protect people, but we rely ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'on the most brilliant, the most dedicated , the great forces that I want to pay tribute to this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'evening.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (545.0, 694.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"I completely agree with Gordon Brown about the bravery of our forces. I've been to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Afghanistan four times. Every time you're just blown away by the professionalism of these " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'people. I actually, to prepare for this debate, I went for a run this morning with someone who ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"just got back from Afghanistan this morning, I couldn't keep up, he was someone who'd served " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'for six months and had done an incredible job there. Just going back to the point about how we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'get these things right, one of the things that strikes you when you go to Afghanistan is that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'actually we are not getting things right politically. The south of the country is where Taliban ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'grew, where they came from, that is the Pashtun part of the country. Yet when you see the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Afghan National Army, it is dominated by people from the other parts of the country. There is a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"really big political issue there. We have to make sure the whole country in Afghanistan feels it's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"part of the Afghan Government. That's absolutely key for making sure we can bring our " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'soldiers back home. Not just training the Afghan army and police, as Gordon said, vital though ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that is, we need a political settlement as well to help make sure we can come home.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (72.0, 325.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I think Stuart's point, which he's pinpointing, even if you decide, even if we as a country decide " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to undertake a mission like that again, there is no point deciding you want to do it, unless you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'know how. Unless we can provide the necessary resources. I remember when I was in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Helmand visiting the troops there, I talked to some mechanics, who look after the vehicles. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'They were telling me that they had been on a convoy previously which normally just takes one ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'day to from one place to another, it took them a week, because every time the vehicle broke ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"down in the sands there, they didn't have the necessary parts, they had to take parts from " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'other vehicles. So, if we do this again, we cannot, cannot, cannot allow eight years to elapse, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"which is what's happened, until proper equipment is finally been provided to our very, very " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'courageous servicemen and servicewomen.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Look, we've had to change our tactics all the time because of what the Taliban has been " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'doing. Originally, they wanted to win a face-to-face war with us, fighting person-to-person. Now ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'they use explosive devices, these explosive devices are designed to scare as well as to maim ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'our own troops. We have had to change our tactics and therefore bring in the explosive ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'experts, bring in the metal detectors, bring in the drones to survey the land, make sure we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'have the proper intelligence, go into Pakistan and deal with the making of bombs as well. All ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"these things have had to happen and we've had to change our tactics again because we want " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to train up the Afghan police and army so we're partnering with the Afghan police. I'd like to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"say to our troops, come back into the barracks and you will be safe. But I can't say that, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'because our strategy in Afghanistan depends on contact with the local people, persuading ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'them they are safe with us, and safe in an Afghanistan free of the Taliban. We have had to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"change, yes, but it's response to the tactics of our opponents.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 115.0), (187.0, 198.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (337.0, 451.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"I'd just like to take up this point about Trident and about our independent nuclear deterrent. I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'think it would be completely wrong to try and trade-off equipping our forces properly today, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"which must be done, with securing our future for the future. I think it's one of the biggest " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"decisions any prime minister would have to take. And we've got to get this right. And I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'profoundly believe that we are safer having an independent nuclear deterrent in an unsafe and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"uncertain world, a proper replacement to Trident, because we simply don't know what the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"world will look like in 40 years time. I think it's a real risk, as the Liberal Democrats say, first to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"be opposed to an independent nuclear deterrent, now to say they do want one, but it's not the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"same as Trident, but they can't tell us what it is. You can't take risks with this. It's really " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'important you get it right.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (463.0, 635.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"If you don't believe me, then believe the several generals who wrote just this week in a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'newspaper saying precisely what I have been saying all along, why take a decision now to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'commit that amount of money on replacing Cold War nuclear missile system, when that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'system has still got several years to run, when those military people themselves say there are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'cheaper and better alternatives, and of course most importantly, when the world is changing. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'President Obama said last week, I think quite rightly, that now the greatest threat to us is not ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the Cold War threats of old, it's terrorists getting hold of dirty bombs, Trident isn't going to help " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you with that. Let's move with the times, take decisions when we need to take them, and at " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'least have this review, which I talked about , after the election and consider everything that is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'possible.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'I have to deal with these decisions every day, I say to you, Nick, get real, get real. Because ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Iran, you are saying, might be able to have a nuclear weapon, and you wouldn't take action " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"against them, but you're saying we've got to give up our Trident submarines and our nuclear " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'weapon now. Get real about the danger that we face, if we have North Korea, Iran and other ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'countries with nuclear weapons....  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 115.0), (578.0, 589.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (647.0, 704.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u' This is extraordinary, to say get real, what is dangerous is to commit to spend a whole lot of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"money that we might not have on a system which almost certainly won't help, when the world " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"is changing, when we're facing new threats, when now more and more military experts are " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'saying that there are different alternatives. You want to hold a review, and you want to exclude ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the one big issue which should be at the heart of that review.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 555.0), (716.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'I thought I would never utter these words, I agree with Gordon. You cannot put off this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"decision, General Mike Jackson said today we can't go on putting off decision. You have to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'make it early, you have to keep your country safe and secure. You cannot rustle up a nuclear ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"deterrent at the last minute as the Liberal Democrat seem to think you can. And it's deeply " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((141.0, 176.0), (72.0, 83.0)) {}
  [
    u'unsafe. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 556.0), (123.0, 146.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"We're going to move on now to the next question, coming from Nicola Tanner from Horfield in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Bristol.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 546.0), (158.0, 192.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u'Given that climate change is one of the biggest global threats we face, what have you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'personally done in the last six months to use more environmentally friendly and sustainable ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'forms of transport, such as bikes and trains, rather than cars and planes. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 483.0), (204.0, 215.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'So, what are you doing personally to tackle climate change? Gordon Brown.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (227.0, 376.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"I've been on trains all the time. I don't think I have been on any more than one plane during " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'this campaign time, I have been going around by trains. And I think actually our high-speed rail ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'network will allow people to get off the roads and also to get off domestic air flights, and I think ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"that's incredibly important. I would say the other thing I have done, and I'm very pleased we've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'managed to do this in our home in North Queensferry, we thought living on a hill with a huge ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'amount of wind, not very good weather in Scotland, as you know, that a wind turbine would be ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the answer. In fact, we found, far better, even in this area where there's not much sun is a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'solar panel. I would recommend people if they can to use this form of energy because it allows ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'us to heat our water in a way that is far more environmentally friendly. Weve gotthe first ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Climate Change Act in the world, we are due to reduce emissions substantially by 2020 and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"2030, there is a lot more to be done both individually and as a community. But we've also got " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to get a world agreement, we've got to work, David, with Europe to do so and work with the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"rest of the world, and that's the way to get environmental emmissions down.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 271.0), (388.0, 399.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. David Cameron.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (411.0, 548.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'When I said to my party we had to get real about the environment, and we to be a party that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'was a blue-green party, not just a blue party. I did actually once get a letter from someone ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"couldn't really agree with this and said, Mr Cameron, if you're so concerned about carbon " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"emissions why don't you just stop breathing? That was the moment I realised I still have some " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"persuasion to do. In terms of my own life, the biggest thing we've done is to have proper " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'insulation in our house and actually really can cut your energy bill and make life cheaper as ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'well as greener. But I would say in the last six months, the biggest change, or the last year, the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"biggest change that I've been able to make is actually coming out very strongly against the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'third runway at Heathrow. I think it is wrong to do that. I think we should be going for high-' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'speed rail instead. We should have a high-speed rail hub at Heathrow. Trying to make sure all ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the flights people take where you could take a train, it is possible to do that. I think it would be ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'a really big step forward.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 250.0), (551.0, 562.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. Nick Clegg.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (574.0, 712.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I suspect I'm like many people, I of course tried to change my behaviour, when I travel up to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'my constituency in Sheffield and back again every week, I almost always do that by train, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"unless there is so much clobber with the kids that I simply can't carry it on the train. But I don't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"do enough. I'm acutely aware I don't do enough, I'm like many, many people, I wish I could and " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'would do more. Part of the problem, because you referred specifically, Nicola, to aeroplanes, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and you're quite right that flights at least when they are able to fly, and there isn't too much " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'volcanic ash around, do create a growing proportion of the CO2 emissions, so we need to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'tackle it. I think what is irrational is the moment you have a tax system which taxes passengers ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"in aeroplanes, that means that planes with freight in them, for instance, aren't taxed, to reflect " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the pollution they cause. You've got lots of planes that are half empty or barely got any " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'passengers at all. If you changed it to a plane tax, you would make a dramatic difference in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'cutting down on unnecessary aviation pollution.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 266.0), (714.0, 725.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. Gordon Brown.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (72.0, 198.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"If we are going to make a real difference, we've GOT to change the energy balance in our " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"country. We've got to remove this fixation about using oil, our addiction to oil, our dependence " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'on oil. That is why our energy plan talks about how we can move with nuclear and renewables ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and oil and gas. We want 15% renewables by 2020, with the world's leading offshore wind " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'power at the moment, and we want to do more in every area of renewables. The question I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'have to ask the two other parties is this, why, Nick, are you so against nuclear power, because ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'it is the means to balance off our energy supply, without having the dependence on oil. And ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"David, why don't you have a renewables target as we do, so that we can use wind power? " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Why are you so against the on-shore wind that power people are trying to develop? You seem ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to support it in principle but in every constituency where it happens, you seem to be against it. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Let's get real also about getting this energy balance right. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 216.0), (212.0, 223.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'David Cameron. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (235.0, 361.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Of course we need an energy balance, and we need nuclear, we need renewables, we need ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the full range. It's a great opportunity for our country to do these things. I think one of the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"biggest opportunities we've got is actually with our own homes. We have a proposal called The " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Green Deal. We want to say to everyone in this country, that you can spend up to \xa36,500 on ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'your home to insulate it and better protect it, and then you can see your energy bills come ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'down. And we will have companies, Marks & Spencers and others have expressed an interest, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to come and carry out that work and pay for it and share with you the reduction in the bills. I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'think that would show people that going green actually can save you money. It can actually get ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Britain working again, it can cut carbon emissions, it can cut fuel poverty. For all those ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"reasons, I'd want it to be a really big part of the first Queen's Speech, if I'm elected as your " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Prime Minister. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 364.0), (363.0, 374.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"The only problem, David, is we're doing it already. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 490.0), (376.0, 387.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"Mr Brown, you're going to get your turn in a moment. For now, it's Nick Clegg.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (399.0, 548.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"Hold your horses. You've asked... Gordon Brown asked me about nuclear power. I don't have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"a theological opposition to nuclear power. I just think it's extraordinarily expensive, very, very " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'expensive indeed. There are some calculations that it would lead to average energy bills ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'increasing in this country rather than decreasing. It takes a long, long, long time to build these ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'nuclear plants. All the experts agree that it would take well into the next decade to create new ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'nuclear energy, which would be too late to deal with the energy problems we have now. For a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'fraction of the money that I think both David Cameron and Gordon Brown want to spend on ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'subsidising the nuclear industry, we could develop mass insulation programmes of our homes, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'our schools and our hospitals. Remember, 27% of all carbon dioxide emissions in this country ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'go straight out of your window, through the roof of your house. If we only used energy more ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'efficiently and also, of course, invested some of the money which would be wasted on big ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'nuclear projects on wind energy and other renewable energies, I think that is the way towards ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'a sustainable future.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (560.0, 686.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"You can't have a balanced energy policy in the modern world, as almost every country is now " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"finding in the advanced world, without using nuclear power. I do say the schemes we've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"introduced... I met some young guys yesterday, and girls, who've been working on an energy " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"project in Wales. They'd been taken on as a result of our future jobs fund. They're in the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"business of helping insulation and giving people advice about the use of energy. So we're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"trying to do this at the moment and we will do more in future years. Yes, we've got to insulate " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"our houses, yes, we've got to have carbon-free homes where possible, yes, we've got to have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the electric car, we're investing in that, the hybrid car, and yes, we've got to develop offshore " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'wind power. But the energy balance has got to be fair. Any party that is now excluding nuclear ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'power, which is already a substantial part of our country, is not really thinking about the needs ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'of a future where we cannot be dependent on these high oil prices forever. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (72.0, 164.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Actually, the situation is worse than Gordon Brown describes, because actually, according to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the government's own figures, we are potentially heading for power cuts in 2017. And actually, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"nuclear power stations won't really come on stream by then, so we have a greater emergency " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and we do need to look at the level of gas storage we have in this country which is much lower ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'than France or Germany. They have up to a hundred days and we have a little over two ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'weeks. We also need to make sure that we get the renewables and maybe even extra gas ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"capacity on stream faster, otherwise we could see the lights go out. That's because we have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'had over the past 13 years so many different strategies and so little action.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 506.0), (174.0, 185.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'This is not the bit for speeches. Trying to get everyone in an exchange. Mr Clegg.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (197.0, 289.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"The one thing which hasn't been mentioned at all which is absolutely crucial to dealing with a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'global problem is acting globally. I remember seeing the television pictures of Gordon Brown ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'sitting, I have to say, slightly on the side-lines in the summit in Copenhagen while America and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"China basically cut everybody else out. I think if you're going to lead on this, of course you " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"have to lead at home, but you also have to lead in Europe. There's no point clubbing together " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'as David Cameron has done with people who even deny the existence of climate change in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Europe. You've got to create strength in numbers in Europe so that we can really lead in the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'world, because this is a global problem which requires a global response.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (301.0, 358.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"But, Nick, you're right, there is no British-only solution and David has to face up to that. You've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"also got to face up to the fact that the co-operation we've achieved, 100 countries have now " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"signed carbon emission reduction plans. We're trying to persuade China and America to do so. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'We need America on our side. Your anti-Americanism will not help us. We need to work with ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'all the different continents to get a climate change agreement.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (370.0, 438.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Just one point on the European issue. There is a bit of a con going on here as well. The Lisbon ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Treaty has just about seven words on climate change. You don't need another treaty for " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'politicians to get together in different countries, you need political will, you need action. That is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'what is required. Instead, what we keep getting from the other two parties is more institutions, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"more regulation, more new agreements. That's not what's required. It's action at the European " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'level and that requires political will.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (450.0, 530.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"Of course you don't need a new treaty, but you do need to at least work with people in Europe " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'who believe climate change exists. That would be a helpful start. On the point that Gordon ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Brown keeps saying, anti-Americanism. I have a simple attitude towards our relationship with ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"America. It is an immensely important, special relationship, but it shouldn't be a one-way " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"street. We shouldn't always automatically do what our American friends tell us to do. We've got " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to make sure we act on the world stage in our interests, not simply at the beck and call of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'anybody else.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 555.0), (542.0, 588.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"And I persuaded the Americans to be part of a G20 that dealt with the banking crisis and I'm " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'still pushing the Americans to take action on climate change as well. But, David, I mean, your ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'anti-Europeanism becomes more and more obvious as this debate goes on. It is the big ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"society at home, but it's the little Britain abroad. I think you've got to rethink your policies.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (600.0, 668.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"I just think they're just trying to frighten you, the other two parties, because they don't want " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'actually a Britain that stands up for itself in Europe. They keep going on about these alliances. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'One of our main allies is the party of the Polish president who tragically died in that accident, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'who both the politicians standing next to me praised as a great patriot and a great statesman. I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'think we can hear no more of that. The fact is, you can co-operate and work with your ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'European partners without signing a new treaty, without giving away so many new powers.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 544.0), (680.0, 703.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"That is going to be the last word on Europe for now. I suspect it will come up later on. Let's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'move on now and a question from Michael Jeans who is from central Bristol.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 558.0), (72.0, 141.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u'Good evening. The Pope has accepted an invitation to make an official state visit to Britain in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'September at a cost of millions of pounds to tax-payers. If you win the election, will you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"disassociate your party from the Pope's protection over many years of Catholic priests who " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'were ultimately tried and convicted of child abuse, and from his fierce opposition to all ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'contraception, embryonic stem cell research, treatment for childless couples, gay equality and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the routine use of condoms when HIV is at an all-time high?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 461.0), (153.0, 164.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"Thank you, Michael. So, do you back the Pope's visit, David Cameron?  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (176.0, 325.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"I do think it's welcome that the Pope is coming to Britain, and I would, if I was your Prime " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Minister, I would want to support that visit and make sure I could do everything in my power to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'make it a success. There are millions of people in our country who will welcome that, who ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"shares the Pope's Catholic faith and I think we should try and make a success of it. Do I agree " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"with everything the Pope says? No, I don't agree with him about contraception. I don't agree " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'with him about homosexuality, and I think the Catholic Church has got some very, very serious ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'work to do to unearth and come to terms with some of the appalling things that have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'happened, and they need to do that. But I do think we should respect people of faith. I think ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'faith is important in our country. I think faith-based organisations, whether they are Christian or ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Jewish, or Muslim, or Hindu, do amazing things in our country, whether it is working in our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'prisons or providing good schools or actually helping some of the most vulnerable people in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'our country. A country where faith is welcome, yes, a visit from the Pope, yes, but does that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'mean we have to agree with everything he says? No.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 195.0), (337.0, 348.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Nick Clegg. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 554.0), (360.0, 474.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I'm not a man of faith, but my wife Miriam is Catholic, my children are being brought up in her " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'faith, so I have a little bit of an insight into the immense feelings of anguish in the Catholic ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'community here and elsewhere. And I think many Catholics themselves feel really extremely, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"extremely torn apart by what's happened. I think they do want to see the Catholic Church " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"express greater openness and repentance. You can't keep a lid on sin, and of course you " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"need to move with the times. I do welcome the Pope's visit, but I hope by the time he does " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'visit, there is a greater recognition that there has been terrible, terrible suffering, there have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"been abusive relationships which have left immeasurable scars on individual people's lives " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and we need a process of openness and then healing. You can't undo the tragedies of the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'past, but you can be open about them so people can start to move on.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 211.0), (487.0, 498.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (510.0, 671.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"I've met some of the people who have rightly complained about the abuse that they were " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'subject to when young, and it never leaves them. It is something that is with them always. And ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'no matter what you can try to do to help, there is always this problem that they have to face up ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to every day, that they were abused, cruelly abused, by people in whom they placed their faith ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and trust. So the church has got to deal with these problems, and it's got to make sure that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'there is an open and clean confession about what has happened, and that we help those ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"people who have been put into difficulty by this abuse. You know, I welcome the Pope's visit to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Britain. And I want him to come to Britain for two reasons: one is the Catholic Church is a great ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'part of our society, and we should recognise it as such, and I hope every British citizen wants ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to see this visit by the Pope take place. Secondly, we must break down the barriers of religion ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that exist in our world. The faiths must come together and recognise they have common ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'values and common interests. They all believe that we should be good neighbours to each ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"other. I'm from the Presbyterian religion, but I support the visit, but I not only support it, I want " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'religious faiths to work more closely together.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 564.0), (683.0, 705.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Before we bring in David Cameron, I would remind you that Michael Jeans is also concerned ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'about the attitude of the Catholic Church to science and also gender matters. David Cameron?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 556.0), (72.0, 175.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Again, I would say to Michael that, again, I would be agreeing with you, and against the Pope ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"in terms of, for instance, the need to make advances in... er... in science. I don't think we " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'should - obviously, you need proper protections and proper rules, and we debated them at ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'great length in the House of Commons, but I do want to see that go ahead. Also, on the issue ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"of abortion. There are lots of areas I don't agree. I don't think that means you should stop " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'someone visiting our country or condemn them. We must try and build a open and tolerant ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'country where we respect people for their different faiths, we bring faiths closer together with ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'each other and we are prepared to have an open and frank discussion about these things. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"That's the only way to go. It's nice to hear that pretty much we all agree about that.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 192.0), (187.0, 198.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Mr Clegg?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 555.0), (210.0, 290.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I think on this matter, we do. I don't agree, I've made it publicly clear in the past, that I don't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"agree with the formal doctrine on homosexuality of the Catholic Church, for instance. I don't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"agree with it at all. It doesn't mean I don't... I think there should be some, you know, uprising " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"against the Pope's visit, quite the reverse. I would like to see the Pope here. I think the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Catholic community in Britain wants to welcome him, but, as we've all acknowledged, that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"doesn't mean one has to subscribe to the every letter and every crossed T and dotted I of the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'thee theology and doctrine of that church. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (302.0, 451.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"You know, on all these big issues, I think we're proving ourselves to be a tolerant and " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'understanding nation. We introduced civil partnerships, and therefore we changed the laws on ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"homosexuality and said to people, if you're gay or straight, you have a place in British society. I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"think for many people, that was a great liberation, and I'm pleased that it has happened in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Britain in these last few years. On human embryology, I've disagreed with the Catholic Church " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'because I believe if you can treat a disease by using embryos that are enabling us to make ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'sure people can be free of some of the conditions that afflict their lives, we should do so under ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the right rules. I'm sorry that in principle there is a disagreement with the church on that. On " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the question of contraception, I think we know that in Africa, we know round the world, that it is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'important to give women access and choice so that they can make their own decisions, and I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'regret the fact that the Catholic Church does not do that. The Pope should come to Britain, we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'should have these debates and we should welcome all religions because bringing religions ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'together is the key to making sure that we have a more peaceful world.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (463.0, 555.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"OK, thank you. Given the degree of agreement, we're going to move on now and take some " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'more questions. That brings to an end the international affairs part of this debate, although we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"may well come back to it in subsequent questions, and in a moment we're going to move on to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the open section. Before we do that, just a reminder that you can see the Sky News Scotland ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"debate this Sunday. It'll feature senior politicians from three parties represented here, plus the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"First Minister of Scotland, the SNP's Alex Salmond. So, please join me live from Edinburgh at " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"my next gig, this Sunday at 10.30. Let's move on now to the next question. This question " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'comes from Mary Slattery from Montperlier here in Bristol.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 547.0), (567.0, 589.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u'Given the scandals of the last year, it is hard to find a person in my neighbourhood who ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'believes in the power of their vote. How do you plan to restore faith in this political system?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (601.0, 624.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Nick Clegg. Given the powers, given the scandals of the past year, how do you plan to restore ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'faith in politics?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (72.0, 221.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"Firstly, Mary, you need to be given the power to sack any politician who's proved to be corrupt. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"It's something I advocated in the past, it's something I put forward in Westminster, both David " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Cameron and Gordon Brown's party didn't support that. They now say, which is good, say they " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"do welcome that. You're the boss, you're the boss. The other thing of course we need to do is " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"clean up all the murky business of party funding. We've all had problems with party funding. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Again, there was a deal, there was a deal on the table, we supported it, to clean up party ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'funding. Yet again, the old parties said no. Gordon Brown wanted to protect his trade union ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'pay masters, David Cameron wanted to protect his paymaster in Belize. I think we all agree on ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the rhetoric of cleaning up politics, but we actually have to act. I'd say one final thing: one of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the reasons why your friends and your neighbours are perhaps right in saying they feel ignored ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'is because we have this very odd electoral system which allows Gordon Brown the Prime ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Minister to be in power when only 22% of people voted for his party last time, many people are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'being ignored and we need to change that as well.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 214.0), (233.0, 244.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 565.0), (256.0, 405.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'I think Mary is saying can a vote make a difference? I believe it can. Yes, we will give the right ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"of recall, so if you don't like an MP for being corrupt and parliament doesn't take any action, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'then you can remove him. Yes, we will give you a right to put petitions to the House of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Commons so they have to be debated if you put them in sufficient number to do so. Yes, we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'want a referendum on the future of the House of Commons and the House of Lords, and you, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the people, should have a vote on a new voting system for the House of Commons, and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'ending the hereditary principle in the House of Lords, and making it for the first time elected ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and accountable. But you know your vote matters as well, because this is a big choice ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"election. We've got to secure the recovery, and it's put at risk by Conservative policies. We've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"got to make sure we have decent public service, and that's put at risk by Conservative policies. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"We've got to build the jobs of the future, and that's put at at risk actually by the policies of both " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'parties here this evening. So your vote matters. Please use it. It is the most important and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'decisive election for years because our future depends on how you vote in the next few weeks.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 271.0), (417.0, 428.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. David Cameron.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (440.0, 589.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"Mary, I think the first thing people want to know is they're going to be voting for a cleaned-up " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'parliament. Everywhere I go in this country during the election, it is simmering and bubbling ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'below the surface. There is just anger about the expenses fiasco. People say, "I pay my taxes ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to have decent politics and yet the money\'s been spent on all these appalling things." They ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'want to be to be absolutely sure this is never ever going to happen again. So strict limits on ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'what can be spent, total transparency so you, the voters, can see every penny. That I think is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the absolutely first thing that needs to be done. I would go on and say we also need to cut the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'cost cost of politics. Everyone else in this country has had to make economies and had to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"make their businesses work better. Why shouldn't politics be the same? I would do that. Then " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'simple changes which would put back in control. I want to see more people involved in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'choosing candidates for the parties, holding open primaries. I agree we need we have a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"situation where you can sack your MP but please don't let's give up the way you can sack your " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"government and throw them out. Let's not have permanent hung parliaments. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 451.0), (601.0, 612.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"Mr Clegg, you're on the front pages... the front The Telegraph today?  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (624.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u" I am indeed for a complete nonsense story. But, anyway, let's put that aside. Complete " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'rubbish. Mary, one of the most heartening things, back to your question about people sort of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'feeling disaffected, one of the most heartening things over the last week, and it is one of the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"great effects of the televised leaders' debates, is that more and more young people appear to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'be rushing to register to vote before it is too late. That is immensely exciting. There are lots of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"especially young people, I hope I'm not out of turn saying you look fairly young, who might be " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'in your position, who feel.. who felt for so long completely turned off by the old Party Politics, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and they are now excited, they're beginning to hope, they're beginning to think that we can do " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"something different this time. that's what I think. I think we can do something different this time. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"But get stuck in, if you didn't vote before, if you didn't register, register. It's your country, it's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'your future, assert your right to vote, assert your right to shape your own future. I think then we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'could make this election one of the most exciting elections we have had in a very long time.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 189.0), (212.0, 223.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Mr Brown. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 558.0), (235.0, 408.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Mary, let me just say, I was ashamed by the behaviour of some of the MPs in the House of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Commons. What they did was completely unacceptable. And no punishment is too great for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'them, if they have to go before the courts and answer for their crimes. We have to be very ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'clear, we want nobody standing at this election who is not transparent and open about what ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"they are doing. Anyone who breaches the guidelines we've now laid down, the Independent " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Standards Authority, should be thrown out of the House of Commons and indeed out the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'House of Lords if they are member there as well. I was talking to young people only yesterday ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and talking about politics, if you ask the question, politics don't make a difference? People " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'would probably say, yes.  But if you then ask the question, ah, but my job may depend on ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'decisions that are made by government, then people say, ah, I might be interested. People ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'then say my health service may depend on how much resources Government is prepared to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'invest in the health service, then people say, yes, politics may make a difference. And then ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'when you ask about crime And it depends on how many policemen are on the street, then it ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'makes a difference. And if you ask about schools and what the standard of your schools are, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and how you are investing for the future, that makes a difference, too.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 271.0), (420.0, 431.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. David Cameron.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 282.0), (443.0, 454.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Politics can make a difference.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (465.0, 614.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Politics can make a difference, Mary, but I would say the politicians in this country have been ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"treating the people as mugs for far too long. They've been sort of saying, we can do " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"everything, vote for us and we'll solve all your problems. Let us pass a few more laws, spend a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'bit more money, pass more regulation and all the trouble will be fixed. It is not really true, it is a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'big lie. The truth is, if you really want to change things, if you want safer streets, if yo want ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"better schools, yes, the Government's got its role, but we've all got our responsibilities, too. We " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"need to bring up our children properly, we've got to make sure we work with the school, we've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'got to make sure we help the police, we have to make sure there is discipline in schools, real ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"solutions to the problems in a country I think come when we all say, I've got responsibilities as " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"well that go beyond paying my taxes and obeying the law. It's my society, it's my country, I will " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'elect some politicians, but I want to join with them to change the country and make it a better ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"place. I think that's a much more honest answer for how we really get the change we need in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the country.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 553.0), (626.0, 660.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'But David, I take responsibility for my decisions, and I ask people right throughout society to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"take responsibility. But you can't run the health service on a do-it-yourself principle, you have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to finance it properly. And I just ask you, why you want to cut... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 195.0), (673.0, 684.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Nick Clegg. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (72.0, 175.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"Can I go back to Mary's question, which is about people feeling switched off from politics. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Something which neither of the other two old parties want to address is this. We have a culture ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'of jobs for life in politics. You have hundreds and hundreds of MPs from the Conservative party ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and the Labour party, from the old parties, who basically know all they need to do every four or ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'five years is get the vote of 20-30% of people in their community and then ignore everybody ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'else all the rest of the time. Of course you then start getting trouble with expenses. Because of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'course if you give people jobs for life, these safe seats for life, no questions asked, then they ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"start cutting corners. That's what we need to change, as well as all the other things to do with " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'expenses... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 298.0), (187.0, 198.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"You're welcome to come in on this. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 503.0), (210.0, 221.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'..and House of Lords, and all the other areas that need to be reformed top to toe.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (233.0, 267.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'All parties have had to take action. We have to clean up the politics for every single party. And ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"anybody who commits an offence is out, they're suspended, out. They shouldn't be in politics " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"at all. Public service is about serving the public, it's not about serving yourself.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (279.0, 382.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'I would like to respond to something Gordon Brown said, which is this issue of responsibility, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'saying he asked people to take responsibility. I think one of the problems in our country today ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'is if you do the right thing, if you take responsibility, all too often you are punished rather than ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"rewarded. If you work hard and save, actually you don't get the Government behind you, you " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'get punished. If you do the right thing... Always in my constituency, you are meeting couples ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'who say, we are trying to get everything together before we get married, before we have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"children, and they feel that people who don't do the right thing get pushed up the ladder ahead " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"of them. I think there's a sense of unfairness in our country today which goes to the heart of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'some of the issues we have in our politics. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (394.0, 451.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'But David, the biggest unfairness is that the biggest beneficiary from your manifesto is the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'3,000 richest people in the country, who would get \xa3200,000 each from an inheritance tax cut. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"if you want to be fair, you don't give people an inheritance tax and then cut child tax credits for " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"middle-class families, you don't cut the child trust fund, you don't cut the schools budget, you " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"don't have a do-it-yourself society... " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 277.0), (463.0, 474.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'The question was about trust.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 502.0), (486.0, 497.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"Poor Mary asked about politics, she's being told about tax credits. I mean, look...  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 320.0), (509.0, 520.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Well, you want to cut tax credits as well. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 557.0), (532.0, 601.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'David Cameron talked about responsibility. Absolutely. We need to make sure people are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'responsible where they have made big mistakes. It is a fact that there are a number of MPs in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'both the old parties, who flipped their home from one to the next, paying from your taxpayer-' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'funded expenses buy properties, do them up, sell them, buy them up, do them up, sell them, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"then pocket the difference in personal profit, who still haven't been held to account. You can't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"move on unless the people who've done something seriously wrong are held to account. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 368.0), (613.0, 624.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"OK. David Cameron. I'll come to you in a moment.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 550.0), (636.0, 681.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Along with... The expenses scandal made people incredibly angry. People also got angry by ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'politicians saying, "I only obeyed the rules." I think they\'re now starting to get angry by some ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'politicians saying, "Well, my party was much better than all the others." Frankly, Nick, we all ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'had problems with this. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 167.0), (693.0, 704.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Sure. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (716.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Whether it was moats, or whether it was politicians claiming on phantom mortgages, or ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"whether it was kitchens and cake tins and the rest of it, don't anyone try and put themselves on " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"a pedestal over this issue. Let's actually sort it out and clean it up and recognise we were all in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'this mess.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 211.0), (110.0, 121.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (133.0, 225.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'No-one should be standing at the election if they are not transparent and tell you everything ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"about what they are doing with their finances. They shouldn't have second jobs either, and " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"that's all too common in the House of Commons. They should be working full-time for their " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"constituents' interests. They shouldn't be in a position where they're not telling you that they " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'will come and report to you every month on what they are doing, holding local surgeries, being ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'held to account. If they are not doing the right thing and are corrupt, you have the right to recall ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"them. That's the most important thing that we can do now to clean up what has been a terrible " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'scandal and something that I am ashamed of on behalf of all politicians.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 558.0), (237.0, 282.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"Of course no-one is blemish-free. Of course people aren't angels. But the point is this. If you " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"are trying to persuade people to invest trust again, which was Mary's question, into politicians, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"then it's just not good enough to just talk the talk and not walk the walk. You can't say you " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'want to clean up funding and then block deals to do precisely that.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 554.0), (295.0, 317.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"OK. Time is up. We've got to retire on this. Time is most definitely up. We are now moving on " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to a question from Grace Lane, who's from Westbury-on-Trym here in Bristol. Grace. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 549.0), (329.0, 352.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u'Having brought up five children, worked most of my life, reached the age of 84, do all of you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'think that a state pension of \xa359 per week is a just reward?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 283.0), (363.0, 374.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown, is \xa359 a week... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (386.0, 524.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"The answer is no, Grace. I'm sorry that that has happened, I hope you are getting the pension " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"credit which is an attempt to make up the pension from what you've had as a result of your " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"earnings being interrupted during the course of your life. What are we doing now? We're going " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to link pensions to earnings in 2012, so every pension will be linked to earnings and not just ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'prices. Secondly, women, and you are one of them, who have not had the full state pension, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we are making it possible for all women in future to have that full state pension. And thirdly, of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"course, we've got to deal with the poverty that people face as pensioners. That is why the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'pension credit, the winter fuel allowance, all these things have been introduced. The free ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'concessionary travel as well, the free television licenses over 75, all of these have been ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'introduced over the last few years, because the one thing that scandalises our society above ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"all else is that we cannot give dignity and security to all pensioners in retirement. That's what I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"want to see and that's what I want to do.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 216.0), (536.0, 547.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'David Cameron. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (559.0, 708.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'\xa359 is not enough. We have got to do better as a society giving people what we all want. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Those that have done the right thing through their lives, we should be giving you dignity and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'security in old age. I agree we need to up-rate the pension in line with earnings rather than ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'prices. The reason I feel I can give you that answer with total confidence, that we will really ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'deliver this, is we have made a tough decision to go with it. Which is to say from 2016, we are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'going to ask, starting with men, to retire a year later. That means we can fund this pledge. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Because we all know we have an enormous budget deficit, there isn't any money left in the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"kitty. So if we're going to make promises like that, and it's a big promise, an important promise, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we have to say how we are going to pay for it. I want to make sure that when we see people ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"going into old age that if you have worked hard, if you've saved, if you've put money aside, you " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'are not punished. That is why we say as well, it is not right that you should have to pay for your ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"residential care, and someone who didn't do the right thing gets the whole thing paid for free. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"That's not fair and we are going to change that.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 195.0), (720.0, 731.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Nick Clegg. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (72.0, 221.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Grace, the earnings link needs to be restored. It needs to be restored immediately, there is no ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"doubt about that. It shouldn't have been broken in the first place, you have lost out for many " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"years, it needs to be restored. Something which I'm sure you're familiar with, which is there are " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'so many other costs which the elderly have to confront, which really do make it extremely ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"difficult to make ends meet. Fuel costs. We have just had a very cold winter for example, it's a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'very good example. I got a letter a few months ago from an elderly couple, who said to me ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'they now found it so difficult to heat their homes on cold winter days, that on those cold winter ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'days, they get into a bus in their town and travel around the bus just to stay warm. That is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'wrong. It is wrong that energy companies charge you more for the first bits of energy that you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"use in your home than the later bits. That means someone who's heating a great big five-" FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"storey mansion is paying cheaper, paying less for their energy than someone who's just " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'heating a one bedroom flat. That needs to change too, so we can give you the dignity you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'deserve.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 211.0), (233.0, 244.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (256.0, 405.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"I think Grace's issue is that every woman should have a full state pension. I think it's right that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we say that that is what we're going to do as a result of our pension reforms. But it's also the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'case that everyone who works for an employer will now also have an occupational pension. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'That is another change we are making that is coming in the parliament to come. When we look ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"at the needs of pensioners, it's absolutely true to say we need help with urgent needs social " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"care in the home. That's what we're introducing over the next few months, so that people don't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"have to go into old people's homes. If they want to stay at home, they can get the home helps " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and the health visitors that are necessary for them so that they can have comfort in their own ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"homes. But I've got one or two problems with the other two manifestos of the other parties. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"David doesn't seem to have mentioned free prescriptions for the elderly or free eye tests. And " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to be honest, Nick has a problem in his manifesto, because he seems to be cutting the budget ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'of the winter fuel allowance this year. I would like them to explain to the pensioners of this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'country what in fact they propose to do.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 276.0), (417.0, 428.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'David Cameron, your chance. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (440.0, 543.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'I just think it is disgraceful to try and frighten people in an election campaign, as Gordon Brown ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'has just done, and as the Labour Party are doing up and down the country. I would like to take ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'this opportunity to say very clearly to any pensioner in the audience, anyone listening at home, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"that we will keep the free television license, we will keep the pension credit, we'll keep the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"winter fuel allowance, we'll keep the free bus pass. Those leaflets you have been getting from " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Labour, the letters you have been getting from Labour are pure and simple lies. A politician ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"shouldn't say lies very often, I say it because I have seen the leaflets and they make me really " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'very, very angry. You should not be frightening people in an election campaign, it is just not ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'right.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (555.0, 578.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"Well, firstly, before I respond to Gordon Brown's invitation, I'm glad you have been reading our " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'manifesto with such care.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 192.0), (590.0, 601.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Absolutely. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 558.0), (613.0, 750.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"There are two-and-a-half million pensioners in poverty, so after 13 years and all Labour's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'promises about giving a fair deal to pensioners, two-and-a-half million pensioners in poverty. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"That's how bad it is. I think we need to, therefore, make sure that we use what little money " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we've got, money is tight at the moment, wisely. And what we are saying is this. The winter " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"fuel payments, the age of eligibility is going to rise, this is a decision which Gordon Brown's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Government has already taken, from 60 to 65 in the coming years. We're saying if you bring " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that forward you could use the money to actually extend the winter fuel payments to people ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"who are terminally ill and disabled, who at the moment don't get access to the winter fuel " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'payments. I think that is fair. One final thing. We talked about social care, we talked about this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"last week, I really cannot stress enough, I think that's one issue where we just have got to put " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'people before politics for once. This is something which is such a big issue, we need to agree ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'on a common approach, that is the only way to provide good social care. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 297.0), (72.0, 83.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Free debate, now. Gordon Brown.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 405.0), (95.0, 106.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'I do seem to be right. David did not mention free eye tests.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 557.0), (118.0, 164.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"Well let me do it right now. We'll keep them. Let me challenge you. Will you now withdraw the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'leaflets... Will you withdraw the leaflets that are going out round the country saying that the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Conservatives would take away things like the free bus pass? You know, you really should be ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'ashamed of doing things like that.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 558.0), (176.0, 256.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'David, I have not authorised any leaflets like that. What I would ask to you say is why is it not ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"in your manifesto that you're keeping free eye tests and free prescription charges. To Nick, I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"would say, if you're cutting the winter fuel allowance, that means that some people will suffer " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"this year. We've already said that all pensioners over 60, all households, will get \xa3250 as the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"winter fuel allowance and \xa3400 if you're over 80. That's an innovation be brought in during the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'period of the Labour government. I would not like to see it cut in one of the most difficult years ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"for pensioners when we're just coming out of recession, but you seem to be cutting in.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 556.0), (268.0, 348.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I've explained before, I don't think there's much. Doing it again. We are actually extending the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"winter fuel payment to people who are terminally ill and disabled who presently don't get it. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"We're doing that by bringing forward a decision that Gordon Brown's government has made. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'But can I just say again before this completely collapses into a game of political ping-pong. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'There are big issues about how we look after the elderly which are huge. They are financially ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"huge, they're socially huge. It's one of the biggest issues we face on how we provide social " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'care. None of us... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 284.0), (360.0, 371.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"The question's about pensions.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 557.0), (383.0, 428.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"Yes, but it's also related to it. It is about providing dignity to people in old age which is Grace's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"question. I don't think we're going to serve the elderly today or those in the future very well if " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we hijack everything with cheap political point scoring when we can work together on a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'solution that works for many years in the future.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (440.0, 532.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'I do think it is about dignity and security in old age to be able to say to elderly people that you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"should be able to if you've worked hard and save hard, you should be able to pass your home " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"on to your children rather than have to use it to pay for your care. That's why we have this " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'plan. If you put aside \xa38,000 when you become 65, you have the guarantee that your home ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"there will be there for your children because you've done the right thing. That doesn't solve the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'whole problem.  That does seem to me a very good start, ending the unfairness of all those ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"thousands of people who have done the right thing, who've worked hard all their lives, who " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'then get penalised and punished by the system.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (544.0, 647.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"The first stage to doing that is making sure people can stay in their own homes. That's the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'urgent needs payment that should be available to all so that they can stay in their own homes ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"without worrying about finance. The next thing we've got to do is make sure if people have to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"go into old people's homes, then there is a limit on the costs they have to bear, otherwise they " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"will lose their homes and they'll have to choose between the care they need and the home " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"they own. In the next parliament, what we're proposing to do is put a two-year limit on " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"payments, so if you're, for example, suffering from Alzheimer's or other diseases and you have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to be in an old people's home for a longer period of time, can't be in your own home, we will " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'suspend any payments after two years for personal and medical care.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (659.0, 750.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Related to that, are those people who look after loved ones who are elderly and need help with ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"cleaning, washing, getting dressed, getting fed. I do think in the past we've all agreed this is " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'something we need to look at, is we need to provide more respite, more time off for people ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'who care for their loved ones in that way. We have got a proposal which will take the money ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'which the government has allocated to its rather flawed bill on social care and use it instead to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"say to those who provide a lot of care every week, here's money so you can take a week off, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'spend some time with yourself on holiday just getting a break. Because I think speaking to go ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'any carers, that makes a huge, huge, dramatic difference to their lives.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 205.0), (72.0, 83.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Mr Cameron.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (95.0, 187.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"The point about helping carers is, I think, we need to help them go on doing what they're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"doing. Talk to any carer, they will say the one thing I need is a break. I don't think we do " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'enough, put the budget in their hands and say, you decide how best to get that respite break, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to get the extra help in your home. I remember trying to do this myself with the care for our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"son. It's incredibly complicated. This whole agenda should be about putting power and control " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"in people's hands, letting them do more, because if Britain's armies of carers gave up, that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"would cost our country \xa350 billion and actually would lead heartbreak for many people. They're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'really heroes and heroines. We need to do more to help them. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 551.0), (199.0, 221.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'We move on to the next question. And the next question comes from Frank Hemsworth from ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Whitney, in Oxfordshire.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (233.0, 267.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u'Gentlemen, given the current financial difficulties facing the country, and now the possibility of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'a hung parliament, according to the polls, is it time to put aside political differences and form a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'government of the best talents from all the major parties?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 433.0), (279.0, 290.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Is a coalition government the best way forward, David Cameron?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (302.0, 440.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"I think we should try and work together where we can. I've always though that's important in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'politics. I helped Tony Blair get his Education Bill through Parliament because I thought it was ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"a good bill, even though a lot of Labour MPs weren't backing it, that helped it go through. On " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the issue of Trident, which we've covered already tonight, we put the possibility of defeating " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Labour aside, backed them to do the right thing. Obviously, if there is a hung parliament, we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'must be responsible, we must try and deliver the best government we can for this country. But ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"I actually, if you want my frank and honest answer, I don't think a hung parliament will be good " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'for Britain because I think we do need quite decisive government to take some of the difficult ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"decisions for the long-term. We've set out some of the things that need to be done to get the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'debt and the deficit under control. I fear if we put them off, we could have a situation where we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'see interest rates rise, we see confidence taken out of our economy. I think we need change to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'get to top of the deficit, to start solving the problems so we get our economy moving.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 247.0), (452.0, 463.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. Nick Clegg. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (475.0, 635.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"Well, I think, Frank, you're right on the simple assertion you're making that when the country's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"facing very big issues, we just talked about social care, but the one you're highlighting is of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"course the black hole in the public finances. It is better if politicians, I know it's an " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"unfashionable thing to say, but it's better if politicians try and work together. That's why I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"proposed several weeks ago, that irrespective of the outcome of the next election, why don't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we set up something which I call a council for financial stability, and you'd gather in that council " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'for financial stability the Chancellor and the Shadow Chancellors, the Governor of the Bank of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'England, the Head of the Financial Services Authority to do one simple thing, which is to come ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"clean with you about how big this black hole is because there's still dispute about exactly how " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'bad it is and then have an agreement on roughly how long it will take to fill it. So that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"everybody in a sense is being open with you, which hasn't really happened until now, about " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"how bad this situation is and how together we're going to get out of it. I do think there is " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"potential for politicians to work with each other. Don't believe all these ludicrous scare stories " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'about markets and political Armageddon if that is what happens.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 266.0), (647.0, 658.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. Gordon Brown.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (72.0, 233.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"Nick, we already have what's called the business council for Britain and that brings together all " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the leading businessmen and women in our country with government ministers to look at what ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we can do. We have the tripartite committee for financial stability which brings together the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Governor of the Bank of England and the head of the Financial Services Authority, and the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Chancellor of the Exchequer. We already have these things. But the key thing is that we've got " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to have an agreed plan to reduce the deficit, protect our public services, and get growth in the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"economy. And I'm afraid that we don't have agreement on what needs to be done even this " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'year to sort the economy out. I want to see our economy grow this year. I want to see ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"unemployment come down. I want to see businesses thrive, and that means we've got to keep " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the government support in the economy for the time being, something the Conservatives don't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'want to do. But I also want to say we should never take the votes of people for granted. The ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"public must decide, and again it's up to the politicians to do what the public wants them to do. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"It's for the voters to decide. You're the boss, it's your decisions that will count. You have the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'votes to make a difference. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 557.0), (245.0, 279.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. Before we go on to rebuttal round, I will remind you this is not a question about co-' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"operation, it's about coalition, it's about people looking at where the opinion polls are, what " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'might happen after the election and want to know your views. David Cameron? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (291.0, 428.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u' Well, I said very frankly, if it is a hung parliament, we will do our best to make it work. If we win ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the election outright, I'd do everything I can to take the country with us on some of these " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'difficult decisions and also try and take other politicians with us because there will be some ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'hard times before we get out of this, actually get the deficit sorted. But there is a problem in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that you do need to have agreement. There is a fundamental disagreement between me and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the other two parties about what we do this year. I think we badly need to roll up our sleeves ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and make some savings this year so we can stop the jobs tax, the national National Insurance ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"tax rise, that is coming down the road. When you've got an economy that is trying to recover, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the worst thing you can do is put tax on every single job in our country. That's why it's over " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"1,100 business leaders have said don't do this. They've said very clearly the threat to our " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"recovery is not cutting waste, the threat is the jobs tax. The others don't agree about that, but I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'badly think we really, really need to stop this tax that could kill our recovery and kill jobs.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 247.0), (440.0, 451.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. Nick Clegg. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (463.0, 578.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"Back to Frank's question, in a sense what lurks behind your question is it a bad thing or not if " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"politicians talk to each other? I don't think it is.  in many other parts of the bog, it would seem to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'be a completely standard... I mean, Gordon Brown has talked about various bodies but none ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"involving the different parties. David Cameron says he'll try and make a hung parliament work " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'but spends all his time in the newspapers this week making those ludicrous claims about total ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"meltdown as if the world will end. The world won't end and it will be your choice. If you decide " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"that no-one here deserves an outright majority, then we'll need to be open about it and talk to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'each other, talk to each other to provide the good government, sound government that you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"deserve, because you deserve a government where we put your interests first and don't allow " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'everything constantly to be hijacked by short-term political point-scoring. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (591.0, 751.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'I want the parties to work together. When I became Prime Minister, I invited one or two ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Liberals to do things, like Shirley Williams, to do things for the government. I invited people ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'who are businessmen and women to come into the government to work with us for national ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'economic benefit. I will continue to ask people to give their talents to public service, and that is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'something that is really important to do. But there is this fundamental position about this year. I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"think we've got to resolve this. I have had to take the economy through the most global " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'financial crisis. We made the right decisions to take ownership of the banks, and the right ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"decisions to get the world together to deal with that recession. Every time, we've said we have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to support the economy through difficult times. Now, what David is saying even when it is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'fragile, he wants, for ideological reasons I think, to take \xa36 billion out of the economy. That ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'puts thousands of jobs, teachers, it puts policemen, it puts thousands of jobs at risk ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"immediately, and that's why they're talking about an emergency budget in June. David, you're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"a risk to the economy. Nick's a risk to our security with his nuclear weapons policy, you're a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'risk to the economy.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (72.0, 210.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"I just think it's another attempt to try and frighten people. After 13 years of failure, 13 years in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"which we now have a budget deficit the same size as Greece. Don't take it from me, take it " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"from the 1,100 business leaders, people who run Sainsbury's, Mothercare, Next, Marks & " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Spencer's, these great British businesses who are going to help us out of recession, saying cut " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the waste this year, stop the jobs tax next year. To go back to Frank's question, I do have one " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'specific proposal where we really think we should come together much more effectively. That ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'is, I want to see the National Security Council sitting as a war cabinet from day one if I become ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Prime Minister. Because, day one, Afghanistan is the top priority, getting it right. I would invite, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'as Prime Minister, the leaders of the other two main parties to come to that meeting several ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'times a year to make sure they were really seeing the advice we were getting from the security ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'services, from the generals, from the Chiefs of Staff. I think in matters of peace and war, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you've got to bring people together better than we do now.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 234.0), (222.0, 233.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"It's difficult to bring... " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (245.0, 325.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'The only thing I would add to this discussion in response to Frank is that if politicians are going ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to talk to each other, then I think what we need to do is be upfront about what our priorities are. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"We need to be upfront about what we would seek in any discussion with other parties. I've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"been very upfront, dealing obviously with the fiscal deficit, we've been much more open about " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'how we would do that than the other two parties. But also tax reform, educational reform, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"political reform. Those are our priorities, that's what we would fight for in whatever situation " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'arises after the election.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (337.0, 405.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'The priority at the moment is making sure we have an economic recovery, making sure we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"don't have higher unemployment. Unemployment in America is a lot higher than Britain. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Unemployment in Europe is a lot higher. I want to keep people in their jobs. But take \xa36,000 ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'million out of the economy, and you lose a lot of jobs and you put businesses at risk. David ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"hasn't thought through his policy and neither is Nick if he's going to argue against this because " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"it's the right thing to do.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 557.0), (417.0, 497.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"No, Gordon Brown, what I'm saying is, if you care so much about making sure that out of the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"rubble of this recession we create a new economy, why won't you, and indeed why won't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'David Cameron, take the radical steps needed to reform our banking system? Nothing has ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'happened which will prevent a disaster in the banking system because of the greed in the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"banking system from occurring all over again. We're the only party saying split them up, make " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"sure that they lend to viable British businesses, here in Bristol and elsewhere. That's the way " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to get the recovery going.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (509.0, 601.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"You can see one of the problems with hung parliament and coalition forming is there's quite a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'lot of bickering going on already. There is a difference here, there really is a difference about ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'what we believe particularly on the jobs tax. I think trying to stop this is vital. What Nick and the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Liberal Democrats are saying is first of all when we announced let's stop the jobs tax, they said " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"it was nauseating, and in their manifesto, they've now said that actually it's their aspiration. It's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the first time in politics I can remember someone coming up with a nauseating aspiration that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'they want to fulfill. But it is a difference between us. We want to stop this job tax to keep the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'economy going. The other two parties are not going to do that.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 192.0), (613.0, 624.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Mr Brown.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (636.0, 704.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"You see, David, I see you haven't denied you're taking \xa36,000 million out of the economy in an " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"emergency budget if you're elected. I would be very very worried indeed. It seems a return to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the old Conservative Party. Nick, on this question of banks, you don't solve the problem by " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'making all your banks smaller. Northern Rock was a small bank and it went completely under. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"What you've got to do is have proper capital controls. What you've got to do is have a global " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'financial supervision system. Alistair Darling, our Chancellor, is now in Washington... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 382.0), (716.0, 727.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Gordon Brown, the governor of the Bank of England... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 421.0), (739.0, 750.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'..negotiating a global financial tax. That is the right thing to do.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (72.0, 164.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'The governor of the Bank of England has quite clearly said that unless you split high-risk ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'casino investment banking from low-risk high street banking, the banks that you and I depend ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"on, you're always going to get this risk that risks will be taken with your everyday savings. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"That's what you've got to stop. It's what they did in the 1930s in the Depression in the United " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"States. I think we need to do something similar. It's what President Obama is doing, something " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'similar, in the United States. And yet neither of the old parties want to even contemplate the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'major reforms needed to our banks. I think we owe it to future generations to make sure that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the implosion in our banking system, never, ever, ever, can happen again. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 533.0), (176.0, 198.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"I think we're going to have to leave this question there. We're going to move on now to a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'question now from Bethlehem Negessi who is from Bristol. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (210.0, 244.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u"I'm an immigrant, and I have been in the UK for 13 years. I recognise that immigration is " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'becoming a problem in the country. What new measures would you introduce in order to make ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the system more fair? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 381.0), (256.0, 267.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'How would you make immigration fairer, Nick Clegg?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (279.0, 428.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Firstly, you need to tighten the borders, Bethlehem, so that we know who is coming in and who ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'is going out. Previous Labour and Conservative governments removed the exit controls, so we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"didn't know who had to leave. I would want to see those reinstalled immediately. I want to see " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'a border police force, we have every right to police our borders. Secondly, I would make sure ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we direct people who come and live and work in the country, to the areas in the country where, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"of course, they have a job and they've got someone who can vouch for them, but also where " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"there is space for them to live, where there isn't unreasonable strain placed on public services. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'And thirdly, we have to do something about the legacy about the problem created by the chaos ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'which Labour and Conservative governments created in our immigration system. That was lots ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'of people coming here illegally, who are now still living, years and years and years, in the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"shadows of our economy. I'd rather get them out of the hands of criminal gangs, so we can go " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'after the criminal gangs, into the hands of the taxman, if they want to play by the rules, pay ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'their taxes, speak English. That is a smart, fair, effective way of dealing with immigration.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 266.0), (440.0, 451.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. Gordon Brown.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 556.0), (463.0, 589.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"When we talked about it last week, Nick didn't tell us he wants an amnesty for illegal " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'immigrants. I think that would be a wrong policy for this reason. It would encourage people to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'come to this country, thinking that at some point we would legalise their presence. I think that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'would be not a deterrent on people coming to our country illegally, it would mean that more ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and more people would come into our country. Our policy is to control and manage ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'immigration. We have a points system to do so. No unskilled worker from outside Europe can ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'now come into our country. If you have a skill, then we will get a British person to do that job ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'advertised in a Jobcentre if the skill is available in Britain. We are gradually reducing the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'number of skills we need to come from abroad. So cooks and care assistants in future, they ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"will come from abroad, they're trained up in Britain. Gradually, we'll go through the skills list " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and make sure those people who get jobs in Britain are skilled in Britain to do the jobs here.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 268.0), (603.0, 614.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. David Cameron. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (626.0, 764.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Thank you. Well, the first thing to say to Bethlehem is that we have benefited from immigration. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'And people who come here legally and come and live here legally, we should be incredibly ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'warm and welcoming and hospitable and build a strong and integrated country, where actually ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we build a strong society together. I think that's really important to say that, first up. I do " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'believe that immigration in recent years has just simply been too high. We do need to bring the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'level down. That is the first bit of fairness that needs to be sorted out. People do want this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'addressed. The other two parties are not actually really addressing this issue. We believe you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'do need to have a cap on people coming from outside the European Union, for economic ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'reasons. That would help to bring it down. Added to that, is new European countries, when ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'they join the EU, we say there should be transitional controls. We were told there would only ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'be 13,000 people coming from Poland, in the end there were hundreds of thousands. That is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"absolutely vital, we are the only ones saying, let's grip this, let's have a cap, let's bring it down " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((141.0, 553.0), (72.0, 95.0)) {}
  [
    u"radically. Then it won't be a political issue. It wasn't in the past, and I'd dearly love it not to be " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'an issue again.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 263.0), (212.0, 223.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'OK, thank you. Nick Clegg. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 560.0), (235.0, 396.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'I think I want I guess you want, Bethlehem, what everyone wants, which is just an immigration ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"system which works. We've had an immigration system which has been absolutely shambolic. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"No idea who is coming in or going out, no idea who's been living here for many years. Gordon " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Brown talks about an amnesty, the only person actually in British politics advocating a blanket ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"amnesty, I'm not, it's Boris Johnson, the Conservative mayor for London. What I'm saying is " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you can't live in denial of a problem which has been created by the chaos of the immigration " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'system in the past. You can wish away, if either of you wish, that there are people who have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'been living here for a long time in the shadows of our economy. I want to go after the criminal ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"gangs who are exploiting those people. If there are those people who've lived here for ten " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"years, speak English, want to play by the rules, want to pay their taxes, why don't we say to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'them, OK, you come out of the shadows, pay your taxes, do some community service to make ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'up for the fact that you came here illegally, and then we can free up resources to go after the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'criminal gangs. I think that is the right balance between fairness but also making sure we have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'a system which works.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 211.0), (408.0, 419.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (431.0, 557.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'I think in the last two years we have seen the introduction, since I became Prime Minister, of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'foreign national ID cards. So anybody who comes into the country now will have to have an ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"identity card. We're also introducing, from the end of the year, a control so that everybody is " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'counted in and everybody is counted out. It was got rid of in the past, it should not have been ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'got rid of. We are bringing that back. Biometric visas mean that we can stop people at airports ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"even before they come into the country if they've not got the right identification. So we're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"tightening up on that. But the big key to the future is the points system. If you don't have the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"points to come into this country, in other words if you don't have a skill we need, don't come to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the country. But I must say, I'm very worried about Nick's policy, because it sends a message " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to people all around the world, if you come to Britain there'll be some sort of amnesty that will " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'allow you to come here freely in the end, without having to be thrown out of the country.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 268.0), (571.0, 582.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. David Cameron. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (594.0, 720.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"Well, the truth is there's a big difference between the Conservative Party, that is gripping this " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"problem, and the other two parties, that I think are just dancing around it. The Government's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"had 13 years to control immigration, yet we've had some of the highest levels of immigration in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the last 50 years. And frankly, I think Nick's ideas would actually make the situation worse. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"There are two bad ideas. The idea of the amnesty... It's been shown all over Europe that what " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"that leads to is a big increase in false asylum claims and more immigration. That's a bad idea. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"And I think this idea of somehow having regional immigration, saying it's OK to come and work " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"in Bristol but you can't live in Birmingham, or you can live in Bradford but you can't live in... I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"mean, it sounds like they're going to put up border controls along the M5. It really doesn't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"make sense. It hasn't been thought through, it would make a bad situation worse, we need real " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'change, genuine change that only the Conservatives are offering.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 563.0), (72.0, 198.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'I just think... Look, this is a really sensitive issue. People feel, quite rightly, really strongly about ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'immigration. People feel very unsettled that they have had no faith in an immigration system ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'which has been run chaotically by both Conservative and Labour governments for a long time. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"All I would say to both David Cameron and Gordon Brown is, yes, let's have our differences, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"but please don't live in denial about what is going on. Don't live in denial about the fact that, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"because of the chaos in the system, we've got lots of people here who are working for criminal " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"gangs rather than for Britain. We've got to deal with that. You can pretend we can wish it away. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"It is a problem. They are here. Now, of course what I'm saying is controversial and people will " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'try and score points. It is at least an attempt to deal with an issue which we have to deal with. I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"don't think we can have another ten years, another 20 years in the old way, just ignoring these " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"things. We can't come up with promises like caps, which don't work. And by the way...  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (212.0, 246.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"Nick, I'm not really interested in point scoring, I'm interested in doing the right thing. If we send " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'out a message to people in other parts of the world, you get an amnesty if you come to this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"country, then you've got a real problem. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 261.0), (259.0, 270.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'What are you going to do? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 554.0), (282.0, 327.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"Net inward migration is coming down as a result of the points system that we introduced. It's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'come down three years ago, two years ago, and is coming down this year. We are taking the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'action that is necessary. From the end of this year, people will be counted in and counted out ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'of the country...  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 329.0), (339.0, 350.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Gordon Brown, what are you going to do? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 540.0), (362.0, 384.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'It would be more helpful if you would support identity cards for foreign nationals instead of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'opposing them.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 562.0), (397.0, 442.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I'm just asking for a simple, honest answer to a big question, which is that because of the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'chaos in the system in the past, we have lots of people who are here. Now, if you just ignore it, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"they will carry on living in the shadow of our economy. You can either deny it, which you're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'doing because you have no plan to deal with it, neither do you... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 244.0), (454.0, 465.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"We're removing them.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 527.0), (477.0, 488.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"Or you try and... No, you can't deport 900,000 people. You don't know where they live.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 244.0), (500.0, 511.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"We're removing them.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 236.0), (523.0, 534.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ADAM BOULTON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'OK. David Cameron. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 559.0), (546.0, 603.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"All I'd say is that the more they argue amongst each other, the more it's absolutely clear to me " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the only way you'll get real change, real action, sensible action on this issue is from a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Conservative Government. It is a sensitive issue, and it needs to be dealt with sensitively and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"reasonably. It's very important that we talk about this properly. But I think the country wants " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and deserves firm immigration control rather instead of the nonsense we're hearing.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 226.0), (615.0, 626.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'What kind of cap?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((24.0, 561.0), (638.0, 718.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'And that would make a difference. And what it would really achieve is getting back to where ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we used to be, where we didn't have immigration questions at public meetings, we weren't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'asked about it on the streets. When you knocked on a door, nobody raised it. Why? Because ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the British public was happy with the level of immigration. We knew that was a level we could ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"integrate and provide good health, housing and schools for people. It's been out of control " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"these last 13 years. That's Labour's fault. And from all I can hear, the Liberal Democrats would " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'make it much, much worse. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
